Reviewed-By: carlos@example.com
PR: https://github.com/example/checkout-service/pull/412

    perf: tune db connection pool for cost optimization — reduce idle connections

    Cloud cost review flagged checkout-service as holding 20 idle DB connections
    per pod × 4 pods = 80 connections during off-peak hours. Postgres max_connections=100.
    Reducing pool_size to 5 per pod to stay under 40 total during scale-out events.

    Cost saving estimate: ~$220/month in RDS connection overhead.

    NOTE: load testing was done against staging (single pod, pool_size=20).
    Production runs 4 pods under peak; concurrent transaction analysis not re-run.

